main event: A yellowish-white object was observed moving rapidly at high altitude in Columbus, Ohio on January 14, 1956.
interesting points: The object made no sound during its flight., The sighting lasted for about 3-5 minutes., Normal weather conditions were reported at the time of the sighting., No identifiable aircraft traffic was noted in the area., The report suggests the object is of interest but no definite conclusions about its nature or identity were made.
